refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.errors;


 If the hexadecimal input string is of odd length an E_WARNING
 level error is thrown.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.4.1

      A warning is thrown if the input string is of odd length. In PHP 5.4.0 the string
      was silently accepted, but the last byte was truncated.

  &reftitle.examples;

   hex2bin example


<?php
$hex = hex2bin("6578616d706c65206865782064617461");
var_dump($hex);
?>


   &example.outputs.similar;


string(16) "example hex data"
